The paper deals with the problem of salient object detection (SOD) in 360{\deg} (or omnidirectional) images, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the issue of fixation prediction (FP) in panoramic contents, which is another subfield of computer vision. The paper involves the collection of a new dataset, which requires human annotation, and the benchmarking of state-of-the-art SOD models, which involves machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of current methods for SOD in panoramic images, which involves a discussion of the challenges of working with 360{\deg} images (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves the use of human eye fixation maps, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and the use of multiple cubic projection-based fine-tuning method, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
